# AI Skills

Use reusable guidance from `ai-skills/`.

## Rules

1. Apply only the smallest relevant skill.
2. Do not treat skills as source-code evidence.
3. Source code, tests, CI, logs, production evidence, and user instructions override skill guidance.
4. Prefer domain-specific skills before compatibility skills.
5. After changing this routing rule, run `scripts/validate-skills.sh` in `ai-skills/`.

## Routing

- Code/file/dependency/scaffold changes -> `ai-skills/skills/minimal-change-review/SKILL.md`
- Completion, fix, merge, deploy, or handoff claims -> `ai-skills/skills/verification-loop/SKILL.md`
- Unfamiliar repository area -> `ai-skills/skills/search-first/SKILL.md`
- Large, stale, or tool-derived context -> `ai-skills/skills/context-discipline/SKILL.md`
- Shared code, contracts, schemas, generated code, runtime config, or high-risk paths -> `ai-skills/skills/change-impact-analysis/SKILL.md`
- Project memory, decisions, architecture notes, lessons, or flow maps -> `ai-skills/skills/knowledge-query/SKILL.md`
- Durable knowledge capture after completed work -> `ai-skills/skills/knowledge-capture/SKILL.md`
- Inbox/project note promotion -> `ai-skills/skills/knowledge-promote/SKILL.md`
- Knowledge-base source, freshness, publication, or drift review -> `ai-skills/skills/knowledge-source-review/SKILL.md`
- Turning feedback, corrections, or lessons into a proposed skill/rule/knowledge change -> `ai-skills/skills/self-learning/SKILL.md`
- Bugs, logs, failing tests, crashes -> `ai-skills/skills/debugging/SKILL.md`
- Code review or merge readiness -> `ai-skills/skills/code-review/SKILL.md`
- ClickHouse tables, ingestion, queries, retention, or event storage -> `ai-skills/skills/clickhouse-io/SKILL.md`
- Dependency, Docker, CI, shared module, `go.work`, or `replace` changes -> `ai-skills/skills/dependency-guard/SKILL.md`
- Release, deployment, rollback, or smoke test readiness -> `ai-skills/skills/release-checklist/SKILL.md`
- CI/CD pipeline or GitHub Actions workflow changes -> `ai-skills/skills/cicd-pipeline-review/SKILL.md`
- Dockerfile, base image, or container build changes -> `ai-skills/skills/container-build-review/SKILL.md`
- ArgoCD, GitOps sync, or declared image version changes -> `ai-skills/skills/gitops-deploy-review/SKILL.md`
- Kubernetes / k3s / Kustomize manifest changes -> `ai-skills/skills/k8s-deploy-review/SKILL.md`
- Secrets, credentials, tokens, or kubeconfig handling -> `ai-skills/skills/secrets-management/SKILL.md`
- Production incident, outage, degradation, or rollback decision -> `ai-skills/skills/incident-response/SKILL.md`
- Architecture, ownership, scalability, cross-team risk -> `ai-skills/skills/tech-lead-review/SKILL.md`
- Service ownership or microservice boundary changes -> `ai-skills/skills/microservice-boundary-review/SKILL.md`
- gRPC, protobuf, grpc-gateway, generated artifacts -> `ai-skills/skills/grpc-contract-review/SKILL.md`
- RabbitMQ events, routing keys, queues, retries, DLQs -> `ai-skills/skills/rabbitmq-event-review/SKILL.md`
- SocratiCode or indexed codebase discovery -> `ai-skills/skills/socraticode-discovery/SKILL.md`
- Go service implementation review -> `ai-skills/skills/golang-service-review/SKILL.md`
- Datadog metrics, logs, traces, dashboards, monitors -> `ai-skills/skills/datadog-observability/SKILL.md`
- Games Labs API/mobile/gateway changes -> `ai-skills/skills/games-labs-api-review/SKILL.md`
- Seamless provider callbacks, signatures, launch URLs -> `ai-skills/skills/seamless-provider-review/SKILL.md`
- Backend interview evaluation -> `ai-skills/skills/backend-interview-review/SKILL.md`
- Frontend interview evaluation -> `ai-skills/skills/frontend-interview-review/SKILL.md`
- Sprint or backlog planning -> `ai-skills/skills/sprint-planning/SKILL.md`

Compatibility fallback:

- Generic API contract work -> `ai-skills/skills/api-contract-review/SKILL.md`
- Generic third-party integration work -> `ai-skills/skills/vendor-integration/SKILL.md`
